  "prompt": "What are the 2014 trends for online video and content marketing?",
  "response": "Here are some key trends for online video and content marketing in 2014:\n\n1. Mobile Video Growth\n- Increasing mobile video consumption\n- More video content optimized for mobile devices\n- Rise of smartphone and tablet video viewing\n\n2. Short-Form Video Content\n- Platforms like Vine and Instagram video gaining popularity\n- Shorter, more concise video content\n- Emphasis on quick, engaging storytelling\n\n3. Video Marketing Expansion\n- More businesses using video in marketing strategies\n- Greater emphasis on video content for brand storytelling\n- YouTube continuing to be a primary platform\n\n4. Interactive and Personalized Videos\n- Videos with interactive elements\n- Customized video experiences\n- More targeted video content\n\n5. Live Streaming\n- Growth of live video platforms\n- Real-time engagement\n- Platforms like Periscope emerging\n\n6. Content Marketing Integration\n- Videos as part of broader content marketing strategies\n- Storytelling and educational video content\n- More strategic approach to video production\n\n7. Higher Production Quality\n- Better production standards\n- More professional video content\n- Investment in video production technology\n\n8. SEO and Video\n- Videos increasingly important for search rankings\n- More video content with optimization strategies\n- Enhanced video metadata\n\nThese trends reflected the growing importance of video in digital marketing strategies.",
